  "texts": [
    "Yet, for those who may have submitted course assignments that were completed with the help of AI, the guideline did not state whether the penalty is intended to have a retrospective effect.On 23 March, EdUHK made a stand and announced for the first time that the university would allow their students to use ChatGPT in all classes, as long as they cite the source in their work.",
    "Being the first local university to do so, EdUHK has also released a set of 6-P pedagogical approachesfoot_2 on the use of generative AI for faculty staff to guide their teaching.",
    "However, there was no specific note regarding how to cite the source or tailor-made guidelines for students yet.The Hong Kong Legislative Council (2023) reported that by the end of March, only 5 out of 8 Hong Kong public universities had explicitly stated their position and regulations on the use of ChatGPT or AI tools to their staff and students.",
    "The lack of clarity creates confusion among students and staff at the remaining universities, who are still in the second semester.",
    "Regardless of whether or not universities support the use of these technologies, it is important to establish clear policies in a timely manner, even if they are temporary for the remainder of the semester."
